<br>
&quot;To their friends, RL names used=ban .. To people they dont like .. RL names used=more flame's for enjoyment.&quot;<br>
<br>
Which friends are you referring to here?<br>
<br>
At any rate, I just think that Fuvi's voice shouldn't have been taken away for breaking a rule that wasn't clearly in place - regardless of whether he'd been banned before.<br>
<br>
If the invisible rule that was broken had in fact been explicitly stated, then a warning, and possibly a banning if the violation was significant (even so I don't think a couple of first names would qualify), would be appropriate.<br>
<br>
So, being that I was an equal participant in the latter part of that thread, and an equal confronting party to Fuvi's arguments, I request that Jaxy and the other Mods please reconsider Fuvi's banning - not because I'm asking nicely, but because the rule he broke was not explicitly stated, because Fuvi DID NOT use the names maliciously, and because mistakes happen and can be forgiven - we understand that the action was taken in the interest of protecting the RL privacy of users of this board, however this is not a case of someone using RL information to cause harm to someone else.  <br>
<br>
If it seems ironic that I'm saying this stuff in the &quot;defense&quot; of someone I've argued at length with, it's not.  The rules that govern any system of &quot;crime and punishment&quot; should ensure that the worst &quot;apparent&quot; offender gets the fairest possible treatment.<br>
<br>
Just give him a warning and give him his voice back please.<br>
